pubchem_description: The Taxonomy database is a curated classification and nomenclature for all of the organisms in the public sequence databases. This currently represents about 10% of the described species of life on the planet.

Note that this is a condensed classification based on common taxonomic ranks, i.e. superkingdom (domain) > kingdom > phylum > class > order > family > genus > species. As the full NCBI Taxonomy tree is huge, nodes and/or branches without PubChem data have been left out.
